## Description {#details}

The lattice value type used by our custom lattice function.

It holds the lattice state, and a set of functions.

Definition at line 57 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/calledvaluepropagation-cpp">CalledValuePropagation.cpp</a>.

## Private Member Attributes

### Functions {#af33eafd9b0aa8b46c991d95f98e64d78}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::vector&lt;Function &#42;&gt; anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;CalledValuePropagation.cpp&#125;::CVPLatticeVal::Functions</>}>
Holds functions indicating the possible targets of call sites.

This set is empty for lattice values in the undefined, overdefined, and untracked states. The maximum size of the set is controlled by MaxFunctionsPerValue. Since most LLVM values are expected to be in uninteresting states (i.e., overdefined), <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-calledvaluepropagation-cpp-/cvplatticeval">CVPLatticeVal</a> objects should be small and efficiently copyable.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/calledvaluepropagation-cpp/#l00107">107</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/calledvaluepropagation-cpp">CalledValuePropagation.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
